Before the coronavirus struck Zimbabwe, I hid behind work, carrying on like nothing happened.I couldn’t go to church where I would carry all my burdens to the Lord or visit relatives and friends to share my ordeal. My baby’s father and I were together for nearly four years. In the first couple of months into our relationship, he became verbally and physically abusive, and after every altercation, I would lock myself up and weep, replaying some of the gruesome moments in my mind. 

In the second year, I was blessed with a baby girl. Life with him went on as usual but I thought that someday he’d change, that he didn’t really mean to hurt me.  



