Two weeks into lockdown, the abuse increased in intensity and regularity since neither of us could leave the house. 

Before the coronavirus struck Zimbabwe, I hid behind work, carrying on like nothing happened. This time around, I had nowhere to go because of the restrictions. 

I couldn’t go to church where I would carry all my burdens to the Lord or visit relatives and friends to share my ordeal. And with my daughter now in the picture, pretending domestic life was healthy became difficult as she often froze when my partner turned violent.  



